HEADWORD: Noncommittal
<hw>Non`com*mit"tal</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A state of not
being committed or pledged; forbearance or refusal to commit one's self.
Also used adjectively.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>noncommital</ent>⟦br⟧
